    • range

      public static Sequence<Integer> range(int toExclusive)
      Constructs a sequence of integers starting at 0, with the last element being toExclusive-1.

      range(3) === of(0, 1, 2)

      Parameters:
      toExclusive - the number that would come right after the last value of the sequence
      Returns:
      a new sequence of integers starting at 0, and ending just before the given number

    • range

      public static Sequence<Integer> range(int from, int toExclusive)
      Constructs a sequence of integers starting at from, with the last element being toExclusive - 1.

      range(1, 3) === of(1, 2)

      Parameters:
      from - the value of the first element
      toExclusive - the number that would come right after the last value of the sequence

    • range

      public static Sequence<Integer> range(int from, int toExclusive, int step)
      Constructs a sequence of integers starting at from, with the last element being toExclusive - 1 with each element being previousElement + step.

      range(0, 8, 2) === of(0, 2, 4, 6)

      Parameters:
      from - the value of the first element
      toExclusive - the number that would come right after the last value of the sequence
      step - the difference between an element of the sequence and its predecessor

    • range

      public static Sequence<Double> range(double from, double toExclusive, double step)
      Constructs a sequence of floating point numbers starting at from, with the last element being < toExclusive with each element being previousElement + step.

      range(0, 1, 0.2) === of(0.0, 0.2, 0.4, 0.6, 0.8)

      Parameters:
      from - the value of the first element
      toExclusive - the number which all elements of the sequence are less than by at most step
      step - the difference between an element of the sequence and its predecessor

    • rangeClosed

      public static Sequence<Integer> rangeClosed(int from, int to)
      Constructs a sequence of integers starting at from, with the last element being toExclusive.

      rangeClosed(1, 3) === of(1, 2, 3)

      Parameters:
      from - the value of the first element
      to - the value of the last element

    • rangeClosed

      public static Sequence<Integer> rangeClosed(int from, int to, int step)
      Constructs a sequence of integers starting at from, with the last element being toExclusive.

      range(0, 8, 2) === of(0, 2, 4, 6, 8)

      Parameters:
      from - the value of the first element
      to - the value of which the last element is less than or equal
      step - the difference between an element of the sequence and its predecessor

    • rangeClosed

      public static Sequence<Character> rangeClosed(char from, char to)

      rangeClosed('a', 'd') === of('a', 'b','c','d')

      Parameters:
      from - the value of the first element
      to - the value of the last element

      public static <A, B> Pair<Sequence<A>,Sequence<B>> unzip(Sequence<Pair<A,B>> seq)
      Unzips the element of a given sequence by mapping them to a pair of distinct sequences.
      Type Parameters:

      B - Type of the Pair.second() of the elements of the original sequence
      Parameters:
